<h1>Cybersecurity Internship Plans Compilation</h1>

<section>
  <h2>1. Web Application & API Security</h2>
  <p><strong>Duration:</strong> 12 Weeks<br/>
  <strong>Focus:</strong> Secure web application design, testing, API security, threat modeling.</p>

  <h3>Month 1 - Foundations:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Web application basics, OWASP Top 10</li>
    <li>API security concepts (REST, GraphQL, OAuth2)</li>
    <li>Hands-on: Vulnerability scanning, Burp Suite intro</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Month 2 - Advanced Testing:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Manual testing techniques, fuzzing, authentication testing</li>
    <li>API testing and securing microservices</li>
    <li>Hands-on: Exploit XSS, SQLi, and API flaws</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Month 3 - Automation and Reporting:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Automation with scripting and CI/CD integration</li>
    <li>Writing security reports and remediation advice</li>
    <li>Final project: Secure an API and present findings</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Tools:</strong> Burp Suite, OWASP ZAP, Postman, GitHub Actions, Python</p>

  <div class="resources">
    <strong>Optional Resources:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://owasp.org/www-project-web-security-testing-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OWASP Web Security Testing Guide</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.apisecurity.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">API Security Best Practices</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>2. Security Operations Center (SOC)</h2>
  <p><strong>Duration:</strong> 12 Weeks<br/>
  <strong>Focus:</strong> Monitoring, alerting, log analysis, incident triage.</p>

  <h3>Month 1 - SOC Fundamentals:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Introduction to SOC roles, SIEM basics (Splunk/ELK)</li>
    <li>Log sources and log formats</li>
    <li>Hands-on: Ingest logs, create dashboards</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Month 2 - Incident Detection:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Threat hunting, alert tuning, MITRE ATT&CK framework</li>
    <li>Use case development and investigation</li>
    <li>Hands-on: Analyze alerts, hunt threats</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Month 3 - Automation & Reporting:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>SOAR concepts, automate common tasks</li>
    <li>Incident response collaboration</li>
    <li>Final project: Build detection playbook and simulate incident response</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Tools:</strong> Splunk, ELK Stack, QRadar, MITRE ATT&CK Navigator</p>

  <div class="resources">
    <strong>Optional Resources:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://attack.mitre.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MITRE ATT&CK Framework</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.splunk.com/en_us/training.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Splunk Fundamentals</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>3. Incident Response</h2>
  <p><strong>Duration:</strong> 12 Weeks<br/>
  <strong>Focus:</strong> Detecting, analyzing, and responding to security incidents.</p>

  <h3>Month 1 - Incident Response Basics:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>IR lifecycle, preparation and identification</li>
    <li>Forensics fundamentals, collecting volatile data</li>
    <li>Hands-on: Capture memory, disk images</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Month 2 - Analysis & Containment:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Malware analysis basics, IOC development</li>
    <li>Containment strategies and eradication</li>
    <li>Hands-on: Analyze malware samples, build IOCs</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Month 3 - Recovery & Lessons Learned:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Recovery plans, post-mortem reporting</li>
    <li>Threat actor tracking and attribution</li>
    <li>Final project: Full incident simulation and report</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Tools:</strong> Volatility, Wireshark, Sysinternals, VirusTotal</p>

  <div class="resources">
    <strong>Optional Resources:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://www.sans.org/reading-room/whitepapers/incident/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SANS Incident Handler's Handbook</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.volatilityfoundation.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Volatility Framework</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>4. Threat Intelligence</h2>
  <p><strong>Duration:</strong> 12 Weeks<br/>
  <strong>Focus:</strong> Collecting, analyzing, and operationalizing threat data.</p>

  <h3>Month 1 - Threat Intel Fundamentals:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Intelligence lifecycle, data sources</li>
    <li>OSINT tools and techniques</li>
    <li>Hands-on: Collect and analyze threat data</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Month 2 - Analysis & Reporting:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>TTPs, Indicators of Compromise (IOCs)</li>
    <li>Threat actor profiling</li>
    <li>Hands-on: Produce intelligence reports</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Month 3 - Integration & Automation:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>TI platforms and sharing (MISP, STIX/TAXII)</li>
    <li>Automate intel feeds and alerting</li>
    <li>Final project: Develop and present threat intelligence product</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Tools:</strong> MISP, Maltego, OpenCTI, STIX/TAXII</p>

  <div class="resources">
    <strong>Optional Resources:</strong>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://www.misp-project.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MISP Project</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.opencti.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenCTI</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>5. Security Engineer</h2>
  <p><strong>Duration:</strong> 12 Weeks<br/>
  <strong>Focus:</strong> Building and maintaining security infrastructure and tools.</p>

  <h3>Month 1 - Security Architecture Basics:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Network security design, endpoint protection</li>
    <li>Identity and Access Management (IAM)</li>
    <li>Hands-on: Deploy firewall rules, IAM policies</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Month 2 - Automation & Tooling:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Scripting and security automation</li>
    <li>Vulnerability management systems</li>
    <li>Hands-on: Automate patching and scanning</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Month 3 - Advanced Security Engineering:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Secure DevOps principles</li>
    <li>Incident detection tooling and monitoring</li>
    <li>Final project: Build a secure network lab</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Tools:</strong> Python, Ansible, Nessus, Splunk</p>

  <div class="resources">
    <strong>Optional
